    "body": "Thanks a lot for reporting @SylTi! ðŸ˜„ \r\n\r\nTechnically, this is marked as `SHOULD` in the standard (as opposed to `MUST`), so I'd say `MintableToken` is compliant regardless. However, as we've discussed in [Slack](http://slack.openzeppelin.org/), the `Transfer` event seems to be picked up by Etherscan to show balances in their ERC20 web interface. For this reason we think it would be particularly beneficial to add the event.\r\n\r\nWe can still emit a `Mint` event, though. And we should for backward compatibility.\r\n\r\nWe'll be happy to accept your PR!",
